A collection of Ethiopic fonts under the Gurage typeface preference as established by Fekede Menuta, and adopted by the Gurage Zone Tourism and Communication Bureau in Hidar 2006EC (December 2013) and endorsed by the Gurage Zone Administration Council in 2018. The orthography has been deployed into the Gurage Zone public school system at the start of the 2013EC school year (September 2020).

Version 1.1.0 of the collection is compliant with the Unicode 14 "Ethiopic Extended B" range which encodes the 28 additional letters of the orthography.
